description: The Birmingham-Southern College's baseball team is scheduled to play in the College World Series on May 31 — the same day their school is set to shut down permanently.
title: Birmingham-Southern makes the College World Series, even as the school closes

description: Hundreds of thousands of people across the region had no power on Sunday, and other states were preparing for severe weather as the storm system moved east.
title: At least 14 are dead after tornadoes rip through parts of Texas, Oklahoma, Arkansas

description: Seventy percent of the money for general election ads has been spent in just seven states. Here's what the campaigns are focused on.
title: Ad spending shows where the presidential campaign is really taking place

description: There is a growing number of Christians around the world looking to visit Israel, driven by the desire to show support for the country and Jews as popular support for Israel falters.
title: Conservative Christians are lending support — and cash — to Israel at war

description: "Okalolies" ring in the new year on the world's most remote inhabited island by visiting the population of not quite 250 in masks and making mischief, an annual chance for the community to come together.
title: The Okalolies of Old Year's Night: Celebrating tradition on the world's most remote inhabited island

description: You may have noticed YouTube suggesting videos with Lawrence of Arabia-length runtimes. Because nerds are gonna nerd, and well-made work draws an audience, even if it's a time commitment.
title: Who has time to watch a 4-hour YouTube video? Millions of us, it turns out

description: Murray pulled out of the Charles Schwab Challenge in Fort Worth a day before his death. No cause of death was given. He spoke openly about his battle with mental health and excessive alcohol use.
title: Grayson Murray, a 2-time PGA Tour winner, dies at 30
